df["InvoiceDate"] = pd.to_datetime(df["InvoiceDate"])
def get_month(x): return dt.datetime(x.year, x.month, 1)
df["InvoiceMonth"] = df["InvoiceDate"].apply(get_month)
In [ ]:
# Tao cot thang dau tien khach hang thuc hien mua hang
grouping = df.groupby('CustomerID')['InvoiceMonth']
df['CohortMonth'] = grouping.transform('min')
In [ ]:
def get_date_int(df, column):
    year = df[column].dt.year
    month = df[column].dt.month
    day = df[column].dt.day
    return year, month, day
In [ ]:
# Tao so luot mua hang so voi lan mua truoc do
invoice_year, invoice_month, _ = get_date_int(df, 'InvoiceMonth')
cohort_year, cohort_month, _ = get_date_int(df, 'CohortMonth')
years_difference = invoice_year - cohort_year
months_difference = invoice_month - cohort_month
df['CohortIndex'] = years_difference * 12 + months_difference + 1

# Aggregate data on a customer lavel
datamart = df.groupby(['CustomerID']).agg({
    'InvoiceDate': lambda x: (snapshot_date - x.max()).days, # Khoang thoi gian mua hang gan nhat
    'InvoiceNo': 'count', # So hoa don
    'TotalSum': 'sum' # Tong chi tieu
})

datamart.rename(columns={'InvoiceDate': 'Recency',
                         'InvoiceNo': 'Frequency',
                         'TotalSum': 'MonetaryValue'}, inplace=True)

RECENCY QUARTILE¶

In [ ]:
r_labels = range(4,0,-1)
r_quartiles = pd.qcut(datamart['Recency'],4, labels=r_labels)
datamart = datamart.assign(R = r_quartiles.values)
In [ ]:
f_labels = range(1,5)
m_labels = range(1,5)
f_quartiles = pd.qcut(datamart['Frequency'], 4, labels=f_labels)
m_quartiles = pd.qcut(datamart['MonetaryValue'], 4, labels=m_labels)
datamart = datamart.assign(F = f_quartiles.values)
datamart = datamart.assign(M = m_quartiles.values)

Build RFM segment and RFM score¶

In [ ]:
def join_frm(x):
  return str(x['R'])+ str(x['F'])+ str(x['M'])
datamart['RFM_Segment'] = datamart.apply(join_frm, axis=1)
datamart['RFM_Score'] = datamart[['R','F','M']].sum(axis=1)

In [ ]:
# Xu dung RFM_Score de nhom khach hang thanh Vang, Bac, Dong
def degment_me(df):
    if df['RFM_Score'] >= 9:
        return 'Gold'
    elif (df['RFM_Score'] >= 5) and (df['RFM_Score'] < 9):
        return 'Silver'
    else:
        return 'Bronze'

datamart['General_Segment'] = datamart.apply(degment_me,axis=1)

datamart.groupby('General_Segment').agg({
    'Recency': 'mean',
    'Frequency': 'mean',
    'MonetaryValue': ['mean','count']
}).round(1)
